column5: I was out on Lake Simcoe again last week, and I have been having decent success. Wednesday I was in a friend's hut in 69 ft of water and Thursday I was in my portable in 83ft, mixed bag both days. Spreaders for the whities seemed to work well, and my small #12 treble with live shiner landed a few lakers too.  Here's a video of the day's action:    Hope you enjoy!
Some nice fish, love seeing the videos
Cool video.  I like the the big sigh when you had a hard time pulling the fish out of the hole  Joey
That's some nice action footage redsfishin Truly enjoyed watching it Thanks for sharing Leechman
Thanks for the responses! I was out on Monday on got some very cool unique footage. I'll post it next week.
